n voting on blockchain - so if a bad actor has a change that would cause a fork, the bad actor loses the vote regardless of how many nodes they have\n\nEssentially, this guards against bad forks being introduced into the default network. But what happens if a user lowers the default threshold?\n\n- User and all of the nodes that they run get a reputation as low as the threshold they set\n- When a fork vote comes up, they lose the vote\n\nIt's a self balancing system that adjusts for bad actors.","timestamp":"2026-03-05T10:46:29.117000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"tts":false,"mention_everyone":false,"mentions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"reactions":[{"emoji":{"id":null,"name":"👍"},"count":1,"count_details":{"burst":0,"normal":1},"burst_colors":[],"me_burst":false,"burst_me":false,"me":true,"burst_count":0}],"pinned":false,"type":0,"flags":0,"components":[],"position":0,"userName":"xorsense"},{"id":"1478902839651729500","channel_id":"1474714869172277302","author":{"id":"1470753607325450271","username":"ymsvz","avatar":"22cca898691daf0b00d0d176406875d4","discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"YMSVZ","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":null,"banner_color":null,"clan":null,"primary_guild":null},"content":"could you explain more not needing validator nodes, i was under assumption it was for validating index and blockchain. of course i think it would be better to not need a validator, but how does this relate to reputation. im trying my best i promise hahaha","timestamp":"2026-03-04T23:51:53.659000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"tts":false,"mention_everyone":false,"mentions":[{"id":"302973705452257281","username":"xorsense","avatar":"cb11971578a5b1dc733875667b838997","discriminator":"0","public_flags":0,"flags":0,"banner":null,"accent_color":null,"global_name":"m3talsmith","avatar_decoration_data":null,"collectibles":null,"display_name_styles":{"font_id":8,"effect_id":3,"co